        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 2.—Dorsal, ventral, and lateral views of skull and lateral views of right and left mandible, respectively, of an adult female Solenodon paradoxus (Smithsonian Institution United States National Museum 217255) from near La Vega, Dominican Republic. The channel for the transport of venom is evident in i2 in the lower panel. Greatest length of skull is 86.6mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/5033334/files/figure.png" .

